1201.definition: [δεσμωτήριον] from a derivative of {{G1199}} (equivalent to {{G1196}}); a place of bondage, i.e. a dungeon

1202.definition: [δεσμώτης] from the same as {{G1201}}; (passively) a captive

1203.definition: [δεσπότης] perhaps from {{G1210}} and πόσις (a husband); an absolute ruler ("despot")

1204.definition: [δεῦρο] of uncertain affinity; here; used also imperative hither!; and of time, hitherto

1205.definition: [δεῦτε] from {{G1204}} and an imperative form of εἶμι (to go); come hither!

1206.definition: [δευτεραῖος] from {{G1208}}; secondary, i.e. (specially) on the second day

1207.definition: [δευτερόπρωτος] from {{G1208}} and {{G4413}}; second-first, i.e. (specially) a designation of the Sabbath immediately after the Paschal week (being the second after Passover day, and the first of the seven Sabbaths intervening before Pentecost)

1208.definition: [δεύτερος] as the comparative of {{G1417}}; (ordinal) second (in time, place, or rank; also adverb)

1209.definition: [δέχομαι] middle voice of a primary verb; to receive (in various applications, literally or figuratively) Compare {{G2983}}.

1210.definition: [δέω] a primary verb; to bind (in various applications, literally or figuratively) See also {{G1163}}, {{G1189}}.

1211.definition: [δή] probably akin to {{G1161}}; a particle of emphasis or explicitness; now, then, etc.

1215.definition: [δημηγορέω] from a compound of {{G1218}} and {{G58}}; to be a people-gatherer, i.e. to address a public assembly

1216.definition: [Δημήτριος] from Δημήτηρ (Ceres); Demetrius, the name of an Ephesian and of a Christian

1217.definition: [δημιουργός] from {{G1218}} and {{G2041}}; a worker for the people, i.e. mechanic (spoken of the Creator)

1218.definition: [δῆμος] from {{G1210}}; the public (as bound together socially)

1219.definition: [δημόσιος] from {{G1218}}; public; (feminine singular dative case as adverb) in public

1220.definition: [δηνάριον] of Latin origin; a denarius (or ten asses)

1221.definition: [δήποτε] from {{G1211}} and {{G4218}}; a particle of generalization; indeed, at any time

1222.definition: [δήπου] from {{G1211}} and {{G4225}}; a particle of asseveration; indeed doubtless

1223.definition: [διά] a primary preposition denoting the channel of an act; through (in very wide applications, local, causal, or occasional) In composition it retains the same general importance.

1224.definition: [διαβαίνω] from {{G1223}} and the base of {{G939}}; to cross

1226.definition: [διαβεβαιόομαι] middle voice of a compound of {{G1223}} and {{G950}}; to confirm thoroughly (by words), i.e. asseverate

1227.definition: [διαβλέπω] from {{G1223}} and {{G991}}; to look through, i.e. recover full vision

1229.definition: [διαγγέλλω] from {{G1223}} and the base of {{G32}}; to herald thoroughly

1231.definition: [διαγινώσκω] from {{G1223}} and {{G1097}}; to know thoroughly, i.e. ascertain exactly

1234.definition: [διαγογγύζω] from {{G1223}} and {{G1111}}; to complain throughout a crowd

1236.definition: [διάγω] from {{G1223}} and {{G71}}; to pass time or life

1237.definition: [διαδέχομαι] from {{G1223}} and {{G1209}}; to receive in turn, i.e. (figuratively) succeed to

1238.definition: [διάδημα] from a compound of {{G1223}} and {{G1210}}; a "diadem" (as bound about the head) Compare {{G4735}}.

1239.definition: [διαδίδωμι] from {{G1223}} and {{G1325}}; to give throughout a crowd, i.e. deal out; also to deliver over (as to a successor)

1242.definition: [διαθήκη] from {{G1303}}; properly, a disposition, i.e. (specially) a contract (especially a devisory will)

1244.definition: [διαιρέω] from {{G1223}} and {{G138}}; to separate, i.e. distribute

1245.definition: [διακαθαρίζω] from {{G1223}} and {{G2511}}; to cleanse perfectly, i.e. (specially) winnow

1246.definition: [διακατελέγχομαι] middle voice from {{G1223}} and a compound of {{G2596}} and {{G1651}}; to prove downright, i.e. confute

1247.definition: [διακονέω] from {{G1249}}; to be an attendant, i.e. wait upon (menially or as a host, friend, or (figuratively) teacher); technically, to act as a Christian deacon

1248.definition: [διακονία] from {{G1249}}; attendance (as a servant, etc.); figuratively (eleemosynary) aid, (official) service (especially of the Christian teacher, or technically of the diaconate)

1249.definition: [διάκονος] probably from an obsolete διάκω (to run on errands; compare {{G1377}}); an attendant, i.e. (genitive case) a waiter (at table or in other menial duties); specially, a Christian teacher and pastor (technically, a deacon or deaconess)

1251.definition: [διακούομαι] middle voice from {{G1223}} and {{G191}}; to hear throughout, i.e. patiently listen (to a prisoner's plea)

1252.definition: [διακρίνω] from {{G1223}} and {{G2919}}; to separate thoroughly, i.e. (literally and reflexively) to withdraw from, or (by implication) oppose; figuratively, to discriminate (by implication, decide), or (reflexively) hesitate

1254.definition: [διακωλύω] from {{G1223}} and {{G2967}}; to hinder altogether, i.e. utterly prohibit

1255.definition: [διαλαλέω] from {{G1223}} and {{G2980}}; to talk throughout a company, i.e. converse or (genitive case) publish

1256.definition: [διαλέγομαι] middle voice from {{G1223}} and {{G3004}}; to say thoroughly, i.e. discuss (in argument or exhortation)

1257.definition: [διαλείπω] from {{G1223}} and {{G3007}}; to leave off in the middle, i.e. intermit

1259.definition: [διαλλάσσω] from {{G1223}} and {{G236}}; to change thoroughly, i.e. (mentally) to conciliate

1260.definition: [διαλογίζομαι] from {{G1223}} and {{G3049}}; to reckon thoroughly, i.e. (genitive case) to deliberate (by reflection or discussion)

1261.definition: [διαλογισμός] from {{G1260}}; discussion, i.e. (internal) consideration (by implication, purpose), or (external) debate

1263.definition: [διαμαρτύρομαι] from {{G1223}} and {{G3140}}; to attest or protest earnestly, or (by implication) hortatively

1264.definition: [διαμάχομαι] from {{G1223}} and {{G3164}}; to fight fiercely (in altercation)

1265.definition: [διαμένω] from {{G1223}} and {{G3306}}; to stay constantly (in being or relation)

1266.definition: [διαμερίζω] from {{G1223}} and {{G3307}}; to partition thoroughly (literally in distribution, figuratively in dissension)

1268.definition: [διανέμω] from {{G1223}} and the base of {{G3551}}; to distribute, i.e. (of information) to disseminate

1269.definition: [διανεύω] from {{G1223}} and {{G3506}}; to nod (or express by signs) across an intervening space

1270.definition: [διανόημα] from a compound of {{G1223}} and {{G3539}}; something thought through, i.e. a sentiment

1271.definition: [διάνοια] from {{G1223}} and {{G3563}}; deep thought, properly, the faculty (mind or its disposition), by implication, its exercise

1272.definition: [διανοίγω] from {{G1223}} and {{G455}}; to open thoroughly, literally (as a first-born) or figuratively (to expound)

1273.definition: [διανυκτερεύω] from {{G1223}} and a derivative of {{G3571}}; to sit up the whole night

1274.definition: [διανύω] from {{G1223}} and ἀνύω (to effect); to accomplish thoroughly

1275.definition: [διαπαντός] from {{G1223}} and the genitive case of {{G3956}}; through all time, i.e. (adverbially) constantly

1276.definition: [διαπεράω] from {{G1223}} and a derivative of the base of {{G4008}}; to cross entirely

1278.definition: [διαπονέω] from {{G1223}} and a derivative of {{G4192}}; to toil through, i.e. (passively) be worried

1280.definition: [διαπορέω] from {{G1223}} and {{G639}}; to be thoroughly nonplussed

1281.definition: [διαπραγματεύομαι] from {{G1223}} and {{G4231}}; to thoroughly occupy oneself, i.e. (transitively and by implication) to earn in business

1282.definition: [διαπρίω] from {{G1223}} and the base of {{G4249}}; to saw asunder, i.e. (figuratively) to exasperate

1283.definition: [διαρπάζω] from {{G1223}} and {{G726}}; to seize asunder, i.e. plunder

1285.definition: [διασαφέω] from {{G1223}} and σαφής (clear); to clear thoroughly, i.e. (figuratively) declare

1286.definition: [διασείω] from {{G1223}} and {{G4579}}; to shake thoroughly, i.e. (figuratively) to intimidate

1287.definition: [διασκορπίζω] from {{G1223}} and {{G4650}}; to dissipate, i.e. (genitive case) to rout or separate; specially, to winnow; figuratively, to squander

1288.definition: [διασπάω] from {{G1223}} and {{G4685}}; to draw apart, i.e. sever or dismember

1289.definition: [διασπείρω] from {{G1223}} and {{G4687}}; to sow throughout, i.e. (figuratively) distribute in foreign lands

1290.definition: [διασπορά] from {{G1289}}; dispersion, i.e. (specially and concretely) the (converted) Israelite resident in Gentile countries

1291.definition: [διαστέλλομαι] middle voice from {{G1223}} and {{G4724}}; to set (oneself) apart (figuratively, distinguish), i.e. (by implication) to enjoin

1294.definition: [διαστρέφω] from {{G1223}} and {{G4762}}; to distort, i.e. (figuratively) misinterpret, or (morally) corrupt

1295.definition: [διασώζω] from {{G1223}} and {{G4982}}; to save thoroughly, i.e. (by implication or analogy) to cure, preserve, rescue, etc.

1298.definition: [διαταράσσω] from {{G1223}} and {{G5015}}; to disturb wholly, i.e. agitate (with alarm)

1299.definition: [διατάσσω] from {{G1223}} and {{G5021}}; to arrange thoroughly, i.e. (specially) institute, prescribe, etc.

1300.definition: [διατελέω] from {{G1223}} and {{G5055}}; to accomplish thoroughly, i.e. (subjectively) to persist
